{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772127286,"nonce":"Wze4NM/i5pMe8rLQGZwuvlCR770=","title":"Hybrid CDE stability: combine fixed decay with Anti-NF gate (v9b)","message":"v9 showed Anti-NF gate produces best early learning (loss 0.55) but cannot self-repair after gradient explosion because gate weights get corrupted. v8 showed fixed decay always recovers but limits learning quality.\n\nSolution: apply fixed decay unconditionally as a stability floor, with Anti-NF gate providing adaptive per-dimension refinement on top. When the gate is well-trained it can partially counteract the fixed decay for important dimensions. When gate weights get corrupted, the fixed decay still pulls h back.\n\nUpdate formula from:\n  h_new = h + cde_update + alpha * gated_feedback\nto:\n  h_new = h + cde_update - decay * h + alpha * gated_feedback","files":null}]}